title: Black Country comedienne Josie Lawrence returning to region
text:
Born in Old Hill, 55-year-old Josie started her career at the Barlow Theatre in Oldbury. She has performed with the Royal Shakespeare Company and played teacher Manda Best in EastEnders. For more information on events in and around the Black Country click here . 
The Festival of the Imagination is being held to mark the University of Warwick turning 50 and takes place on Friday and Saturday. It takes place at the university’s central campus just outside of Coventry city centre. Receive daily email updates from the Express & Star
